<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="62" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1717,2029]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,412,1717,1742]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61">Description. Male</emphasis>
. Body length 
<quantity box="[576,666,1717,1741]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[823,914,1717,1741]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
. Head black with pale gray pollen. Eyes very narrowly separated on face, brownish. Setae and setulae on head black except posteroventral surface with pale setulae; ocellar tubercle distinct with pair of long oc. Antenna black; first flagellomere long conical, 
<number box="[1246,1280,1789,1813]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" value="1.7">1.7</number>
X longer than wide; arista very long, 
<number box="[408,442,1825,1849]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" value="2.3">2.3</number>
X length of flagellomere; arista very short micropubescent. Proboscis long, 
<number box="[1293,1328,1825,1849]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" value="0.8">0.8</number>
X as long as head height, blackish with pale setulae. Palpus black with pale setulae and 
<number box="[1019,1033,1861,1885]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" value="4.0">4</number>
long pale apical setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1717,2029]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,212]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="62" pageId="2" pageNumber="61">
Thorax black with pale grey pollen. Setae and setulae on thorax black; pronotum with 
<number box="[1187,1201,1897,1921]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" value="1.0">1</number>
seta laterally; 
<number box="[1370,1384,1897,1921]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" value="1.0">1</number>
h, 
<number box="[1422,1436,1897,1921]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" value="1.0">1</number>
npl, 
<number box="[200,214,1933,1957]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" value="2.0">2</number>
short acr, 
<number box="[331,345,1933,1957]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" value="4.0">4</number>
dc, 
<number box="[393,407,1933,1957]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" value="1.0">1</number>
psa; scutellum with 
<number box="[638,652,1933,1957]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" value="2.0">2</number>
setae. Legs dark brown except fore coxae and all femora dark brownish yellow. Setulae and setae on legs black except those on coxae pale; all femora with distinct av setae, fore femur basally with row of 
<number box="[372,386,2005,2029]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" value="4.0">4</number>
pale av setae (longest setae slightly shorter than femur thickness). Fore femur 
<number box="[1259,1292,2005,2029]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" value="1.1">1.1</number>
X as thick as mid femur, mid and hind femora subequal in thickness. Wing hyaline, slightly tinged grayish; veins dark brown. Squama dark yellow, bordered with pale setulae. Halter dark yellow.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279710/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" targetBox="[348,1277,305,1495]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1578,1631]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,315,1578,1601]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">FIGURES 3–4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[323,736,1578,1600]" class="Insecta" family="Brachystomatidae" genus="Heleodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helanshana" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Heleodromia">
<emphasis box="[323,456,1578,1600]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Heleodromia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[472,604,1578,1600]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Heleodromia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[620,736,1578,1600]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">helanshana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[745,827,1579,1600]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[745,827,1579,1600]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(male). 3. Tergite 8, dorsal view. 4. Genitalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: epl = epandrial lobe; sur = surstylus.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1675,2024]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
Abdomen blackish with pale gray pollen; hypopygium also blackish. Setulae and setae on abdomen pale. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[263,374,1711,1735]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1578,1601]" captionTargetBox="[348,1277,305,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[286,1301,265,1557]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. Heleodromia (Heleodromia) helanshana sp. nov. (male). 3. Tergite 8, dorsal view. 4. Genitalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: epl = epandrial lobe; sur = surstylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279710/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
Figs. 
<number box="[327,374,1711,1735]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
</figureCitation>
): tergite 
<number box="[472,486,1711,1735]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="8.0">8</number>
and sternite 
<number box="[633,647,1711,1735]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="8.0">8</number>
rather small; tergite 
<number box="[882,896,1711,1735]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="8.0">8</number>
wide posteriorly, with posterior margin slightly convex at middle. Epandrium and hypandrium much elongated and rather large; epandrium nearly as long as hypandrium in lateral view; epandrial lobe long, thin; surstylus distinctly thickened basally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1675,2024]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,284,1820,1844]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Female</emphasis>
. Body length 
<quantity box="[449,539,1819,1843]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="3.4">3.4 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[696,787,1819,1843]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="3.4">3.4 mm</quantity>
. Similar to male, but palpus with 
<number box="[1178,1192,1819,1843]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="3.0">3</number>
long apical setae, all femora with short pale av.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
