<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="63" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,152,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[778,1237,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Brachystomatidae" genus="Heleodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="immaculata" subGenus="Heleodromia">
<emphasis box="[778,1237,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Heleodromia (Heleodromia) immaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Europe, but can be easily separated from it by the epandrial lobe long thin (not furcated), surstylus nearly straight and legs partly dark brownish yellow. In 
<taxonomicName box="[532,999,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Brachystomatidae" genus="Heleodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="immaculata" subGenus="Heleodromia">
<emphasis box="[532,999,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Heleodromia (Heleodromia) immaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the epandrial lobe is bifurcated, the surstylus is strongly curved forward, and the legs are nearly entirely black (
<bibRefCitation author="Wagner" box="[994,1149,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" refString="Wagner, R. (1985) A revision of the genus Heleodromia (Diptera, Empididae) in Europe. Aquatic Insects, 7 (1), 33 - 43." type="journal article" year="1985">
Wagner 
<number box="[1089,1149,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
